=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from enantiopure trans-2-aminocyclohexanol and cyclize with triphosgene or CDI to the fused N-H oxazolidinone core, giving the chiral bicyclic intermediate O=C1CO[C@H]2CCCC[C@@H]2N1 | Step 2: In a separate branch, build the piperidine fragment by installing the N-cyclohexyl substituent that already bears the CH2OCC(F)F side chain on the cyclohexane ring, furnishing the N-substituted piperidine alcohol/handle | Step 3: Convert the piperidine ring alcohol (at the position meant to bond to the core N) into a leaving group, e.g. mesylate or bromide, to give the piperidine electrophile | Step 4: Deprotonate the bicyclic oxazolidinone N-H with strong base and perform late-stage SN2 N-alkylation with the piperidine mesylate/bromide to reach O=C1CO[C@H]2CCCC[C@@H]2N1C1CCN(C2CCC(COCC(F)F)CC2)CC1

